# UI Performance Rules

Keep UI fast and maintainable.

Prefer:
- Optimized images
- Lazy loading below-the-fold images
- Proper image dimensions
- Minimal layout shift
- CSS-first interactions when possible
- Simple DOM structure
- Reusable components
- Tree-shakeable imports

Avoid:
- Huge client-side bundles
- Large unused component libraries
- Loading all icons from an icon package
- Unoptimized hero images
- Excessive animations
- JavaScript for things CSS can do
- Layouts that shift after loading

Animations:
- Keep them subtle.
- Respect reduced motion preferences.
- Do not animate everything.
